The '''Fumetto International Comics Festival''' is held annually at [[Lucerne]], [[Switzerland]].  The festival was established in 1992 as the '''Luzern Comix Festival''', before growing in size and renaming itself in 2003.<ref>{{cite web |title=Fumetto – International Comix-Festival |url=https://www.myswitzerland.com/en-gb/fumetto-international-comix-festival.html |website=Switzerland Tourism |accessdate=31 May 2018}}</ref> The festival has helped Switzerland's comics community unify and grow, crossing the divide between the differing language barriers within the country.<ref name=Beaty>{{cite book |last1=Beaty |first1=Bart |title=Unpopular culture transforming the European comic book in the 1990s |date=2007 |publisher=University of Toronto Press |location=Toronto |isbn=0802094120 |pages=122-6 |edition=Reprint.}}</ref> The festival attracts both national and international guests.  Comics creators honored or exhibited at the festival include [[Joe Sacco]], [[Marjane Satrapi]], [[Chris Ware]], [[Jack Kirby]] and [[Lewis Trondheim]].<ref name=Beaty />

